The paper discusses recent advances in representation learning, which is a core topic in machine learning. The focus is on autoencoder-based models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses disentanglement and hierarchical organization of features, which are important topics in deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper analyzes autoencoder-based representation learning through the lens of rate-distortion theory, which is a topic in neural engineering (cs.NE).
